data.description: LOCATION, LOCATION, LOCATION!  The Village at Chateau Elan offers resort living at its best! Come tour this wonderful, low-maintenance, one-level home with bonus finished space over the carriage-house-style garage. This fantastic home has curb appeal in spades. With a classic and welcoming southern front porch accessed by wide and stately brick steps, one can imagine everything from putting out seasonal decor to simple porch sitting on a Sunday morning. Combine the charming front elevation with lovely landscaping and a driveway that curves around toward the back of the home and you'll agree that 2750 Muskogee Lane is a shining gem in one of Chateau Elan's most popular neighborhoods. You'll also enjoy the rear porch, the very private backyard, and the cul-de-sac lot. Inside, make a feast in the well-equipped, handsome kitchen with beautiful, timeless cabinetry and ample storage. You'll appreciate the ease of meal prep with expansive counter space and the peninsula bar seating for your guests. Choose to take your meals in the formal dining area, or in the area adjacent to the kitchen (and don't forget your outdoor options)! Your common spaces have stunning hardwood floors and this home's neutral pallet is begging for your finishing touches. Don't miss the spacious owner's suite with lovely natural light and a trey ceiling. Don't get lost in the massive closet and imagine disappearing for a respite in the ensuite bath with an enormous double vanity, a walk-in shower, and a soaking tub. There are three additional bedrooms with pristine carpet and two additional full baths. You'll find tile in all bathrooms. This home is a diamond in a crown jewel community. Chateau Elan offers every imaginable amenity and Braselton is a wonderful town where you can easily walk or take your Golf cart to enjoy both the resort and local restaurants, golf, swimming, and tennis, as well as doctors, shopping, sidewalks, the lifepath, & more!
